      "content": "It is incredibly painful to feel that your identity is built on a lie, but remember that this feeling of being a \"ghost\" is a symptom of the grief you are processing, not an accurate reflection of your worth. The fact that you still have colleagues, a history of hard work, and the capacity to articulate this pain means your story has not ended; it is simply entering a difficult, necessary chapter of rebuilding. Please consider speaking with a therapist who can help you navigate this sense of loss without the weight of carrying the entire burden alone.",
      "source": "target",
